%N A372727 Triangle read by rows: T(n, k) = n if k = 0, otherwise n - k*floor(n/k). The binary modulo operation.
%C A372727 The binary operation 'mod' as defined here is discussed in 'Concrete Mathematics' by Graham et. al. on p. 82 and the connection with the congruence relation '(mod)' on p. 123. See also Bach & Shallit, p. 21, and Apostol, p. 14.
%C A372727 This definition is implemented in SageMath, but not in Python. For example, SageMath answers 0.mod(0) = 0, whereas in Python 0 % 0 leads to a 'ZeroDivisionError'. What is often misunderstood is that the operation 'mod' gives answers to divisibility, not to division. Apostol shows that n|0 (every integer divides zero), but 0|n implies n = 0 (zero divides only zero), and thus confirms the result given by SageMath.
